class maxairesources.eval.model_evaluator.ModelEvaluator(train_data, test_data, model: SparkBaseModel, label_col: Optional[str] = None, features: list = [], cat_features: list = [], sample_ratio: Optional[float] = 0.2, pre_process_spark_function: Optional[Callable] = None)[source]

Bases: object

Model Evaluater module to run multile checks for validating models.

Arguments:

train_datapandas.core.frame.DataFrame or pyspark.sql.dataframe.DataFrame

Reference Dataset.

test_datapandas.core.frame.DataFrame or pyspark.sql.dataframe.DataFrame

Current Dataset. Data to be compared. Accepts Pandas or Spark DataFrame.

model : SparkBaseModel

label_colstring

save the report to a html file in the given location

featureslist

list of features required in the training

cat_featureslist

list of categorical features

sample_ratioint

Sample size to convert the spark dataframe to Pandas dataframe for Reference Dataset

pre_process_spark_functionfunction

A function which processes the given spark_dataframe. If this argument is passed then the above samples won’t be applied anymore.

Returns:

model_evaluation_resultsdict

True if Dataset is drifted else False

train_test_validationsdict

List of columns for which drift has been detected

Example:

import ModelEvaluator evaluator = ModelEvaluator(train_data,

test_data, model sample_ratio = 0.2)

model_val, train_test_val = evaluator.evaluate()
